January 8, 2009 5:04 PM EST

Centennial Communications Corp. (NASDAQ: CYCL) reports Q2 EPS of $0.03, 6 cents worse than estimates. Revenues were $261.9 million vs. $256.74 million consensus.

CYCL ended Q2 with 1,091,600 total wireless subscribers, which compares to 1,068,300 for the year-ago quarter and 1,090,400 for the previous quarter ended August 31, 2008. The Company reported 663,000 total access lines which compares to 557,500 for the year-ago quarter.

For FY09:
The Company expects consolidated AOI from continuing operations between $395 million and $415 million for fiscal 2009, excluding stock-based compensation expense (in-line with prior guidance)

The Company expects U.S. wireless roaming revenue to decline by approximately $5 million during fiscal 2009 vs. prior guidance for $10-15 million decline.

NOTE - On November 7, 2008, the Company entered into a definitive merger agreement under which AT&T Inc. (NYSE: T) will acquire Centennial. Under terms of the agreement, Centennial stockholders will receive $8.50 per share in cash for a total equity price of $944 million.

Centennial Communications Corp., together with its subsidiaries, provides wireless communications and broadband services in the United States, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands.[SM]
